This paper deals with the expressive capabilities of a swarm of robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also incorporates psychological associations with emotions, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.MA). The evaluation of the effectiveness of swarm behaviors involves human participants, indicating the involvement of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with the mapping of emotions to swarm behaviors, which suggests the involvement of systems and control (cs.SY).
